    <div class="crowd-tip"><strong>Best time:</strong> Weekday mornings are the quietest period — the museum is compact and corridors are narrow, so even moderate visitor numbers can create congestion in the ground-floor sealing rooms. Saturday afternoons are the busiest. Winter (September–March) draws more visitors than summer as Tromsø's Northern Lights season brings higher overall tourism numbers.</div>
