    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">What are the Polar Museum opening hours?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Open daily 10:00–18:00 year-round. The museum is closed on 1 May (Labour Day) and 17 May (Norwegian Constitution Day). No seasonal variation in standard hours.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Where is the Polar Museum located?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Søndre Tollbodgate 11, 9008 Tromsø — in the Skansen area on the northern waterfront, approximately 10 minutes' walk from the main shopping street Storgata. No dedicated car park; the nearest paid parking is the Tromsø city car park.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Is the Polar Museum accessible for wheelchair users?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">The ground floor is wheelchair accessible, but a staircase without elevator connects to the upper floor. Ground floor rooms are narrow during busy periods. A small discount is offered for wheelchair users as they cannot access the full museum. Ask staff at the ticket desk on arrival.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Can I get a combined ticket with the Arctic University Museum?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">A combination ticket for the Polar Museum and the Arctic University Museum (Norges arktiske universitetsmuseum) is available. Check en.uit.no/tmu/polarmuseet/planlegg for current combined pricing. The Tromsø Pass also includes admission to both museums.</div>
    </div>
